The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation

NATION BRIEFS

 New Delhi: The Supreme Court on Saturday ruled that economic development cannot be reason enough to sanction the destruction of local ecological resources. 

 The observation came in a case regarding sale of a dry lake in Andhra Pradesh. The court said that focus should be on the sustainability of development and policies towards that end have to be earnestly formulated and observed. There is a need to find a balance between developmental needs and environmental degradation, the bench said.

 Ghaziabad (PTI): A 21-year-old student allegedly shot himself dead in the second such incident in two months in the same engineering college. Anurag of R.K. Goel Engineering College killed himself after failing in his exams, inspector Brij Pal Solanki said. 

 Rae Bareli (PTI): A Samajwadi Party leader was shot dead in the town late on Friday, police sources said. The bullet-riddled body of Ashish Kakkad, former city secretary of the Samajwadi Party, was found near a Devi temple in the Feroz Gandhi colony on Saturday.

 Azamgarh (PTI): As many as 78 schoolchildren fell ill after eating the mid-day meal at a primary school in Chakgulara village in this district of Uttar Pradesh on Friday, police said. About 10 were referred to the district hospital from the primary health centre. 




